  "prompt": "Does Cyanogen 13.1 on Moto G3 support VOLTE? If yes, how can I turn on?",
  "response": "Cyanogen OS 13.1 (based on Android 6.0 Marshmallow) for the Moto G3 may have limited VoLTE support, depending on the specific build and carrier. Here are some general steps to check and potentially enable VoLTE:\n\n1. Check device compatibility with your carrier's VoLTE network\n\n2. In Settings:\n- Go to \"Mobile networks\"\n- Look for VoLTE/HD Voice settings\n- If available, toggle it on\n\n3. If no native option exists:\n- You might need a specific carrier-enabled ROM\n- Consider using a GApps package with VoLTE support\n- Some custom ROMs might require additional tweaks\n\n4. Potential alternative methods:\n- Flash a carrier-specific ROM\n- Use Magisk modules for VoLTE enablement\n- Check XDA Developers forum for device-specific VoLTE solutions\n\nNote: VoLTE support can be inconsistent on custom ROMs, so results may vary. Consulting Moto G3 specific forums or XDA Developers would provide the most accurate, up-to-date information for your specific configuration.",
